The paper deals with signal recovery from noisy measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of convex optimization algorithms and hard thresholding also suggests a connection to mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
